                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 822.00/224.]</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul General at
                            Guayaquil</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Guayaquil</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-01-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 26, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>General Montero was sentenced by court martial on January 25 to sixteen years in
                    prison. All other principals were taken to Quito. The mob disapproved the
                    sentence of Montero to mere imprisonment, overpowered the guards, dragged
                    Montero into the street and burned him to death some three blocks from the
                    jail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dietrich.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
